refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
async Awaitable<int> curl_multi_await resourcemh floattimeout1.0
Blocks on only the part of the CURL request that requires blocking, while allowing other execution of the request to continue.

&reftitle.parameters;



  &curl.mh.description;

   timeout



     Time, in seconds, to wait for a response.

&reftitle.examples;



    curl_multi_await example 


  During lulls in network activity, the await curl_multi_async($mh); allows us to pass control to another WaitHandle (perhaps another curl request, perhaps something else), meanwhile the rest of the execution performs non-blocking actions, like calling curl_multi_exec().
